# Code Artifact: android/.gitignore
# Description: Keeps Android module build output, IDE files, packages, signing files, and logs out of source control.
# Programmer: HudLink development team (Brandon Dodge, Zach Sevart, Asa Maker, Jonathan Gott, Josh Dwoskin)
# Date Created: 2026-02-15
# Revision History:
# - 2026-02-15 - Zach Sevart - Added starter Android ignore rules.
# - 2026-04-26 - HudLink development team - Added release prologue comments for sprint submission.
# Preconditions: Git reads this file when commands run inside or below the android folder.
# Acceptable Inputs: Git ignore patterns for generated Android and IDE files.
# Unacceptable Inputs: Patterns that hide Kotlin source, manifests, resources, or Gradle scripts that should be reviewed.
# Postconditions: Local Android build outputs stay out of normal Git status and staging.
# Return Values: Git ignore files do not return values; Git consumes the patterns.
# Error and Exception Conditions: Bad patterns can accidentally hide source files, so source directories are not ignored here.
# Side Effects: Changes how Git reports local generated Android files.
# Invariants: The Gradle wrapper JAR remains visible and trackable.
# Known Faults: Existing tracked generated files remain tracked until explicitly removed.
# Major Blocks: Gradle, IDE, generated package, signing, and log rules are grouped below.
# Line Comments: Each group has a short heading so the ignore intent stays clear.

# Gradle
.gradle/
build/
!gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar

# Android Studio
.idea/
*.iml
local.properties
.DS_Store

# Generated files
*.apk
*.aab
*.dex
*.class

# Signing
*.jks
*.keystore

# Logs
*.log
